Text.Value: What kind of music do you write?
Please, oh, please. It would mean so much to me.

EditorData.NodeContext: sincere and passionate - desperately wants to join the player

Text.Value: Well met. Goblins roughed me up and stole my hose when they heard me singing Hatchling Love.
No.
I've been given a great chance. My song-score: Affairs in Ancient Abeir: Songs of Draconic Love is due to be published in the Gate!
My head is on my shoulders, not in the clouds.
I think they hardly know I exist.
But- agh, I have worked for years on my music, I just have to bring my songbook safely to Baldur's Gate.
I grew up smiling about my little secrets to myself. I would have been laughed at if I admitted to anyone how I felt. It is not our kind's way.
This one, Sky-Swain is about what it might feel like to mate in the air, in the age where wings were yet with us.

EditorData.NodeContext: Intake of breath at the end of it.

Text.Value: Karlach seems like she has so much love to give, if she found the right person.
Well, in all honesty, I ran from Tymanther to avoid my egg-duty.
Stay at the edge of the camp, and stay quiet.
I can't risk another night in the open - the goblins might steal my manuscript next time. Surprised they didn't take it when they lifted my poulaines.
I don't think most of us stop hoping, ever, really. Not even when duty stamps us down.
And that's what the songbook's about. Lost lost, lingering love, never acted on. Never spoken.
Perhaps. But I want to capture this feeling, while it still strikes hot.
Are you any good in a fight?
But I have my whole life ahead of me... Things will be different now I'm on the Sword Coast. I can't wait for what is coming next!
Spoken like someone who's never heard a dragonborn throatsong.
No, and I'm not sure if I'll ever be able to tell them.
Never say no to a bard. They'll write all sorts of mean shit about you.

EditorData.NodeContext: with a subtext of 'duh', then with a soft kindness toward Alfira, who she's met before.

Text.Value: Wyll is such a gentleman, I imagine he'd make an even better partner.
I'm in a big big rush, though. I fear that if I don't get there in the next few days they're gonna print some kobold bone-flute instrumentals instead.
I've been honest enough, so far.
Shadowheart is pure grace.
Why were you travelling on the road, in the middle of the night?
I know we must marry into whichever clan suits our own. And I know we're not allowed to let love drive us,
You're very far from our people's home.
That's quite enough culture for one evening!
There's a special feeling to having love all to yourself, don't you think? For no one to know.
Invite her in, cast her out. I see no difference either way.
I'll tell them when I'm sure they'll say it back.
Mock me as you will, but I have a thing for Gale.
It's too soon for that...
You're painfully innocent.
I've prepared a dense manuscript of new love-chants, to be throat-sung in Tymanther style.
Yes! Thank you - I'll write your name in the dedication!

EditorData.NodeContext: player has let her join - absolutely over the moon

Text.Value: 'Sides, it's hardly ever I meet another with scales as lovely as mine. You're the kind of gorgeous I dreamed of nesting with as a girl.
But I've never even been kissed and I can't stop myself from dreaming.
Oh my! Are you sure? Are you really sure!
Although half the time it's for some Society of Brilliance twat with two left feet writing a book about us.
I met the most amazing, bewildering Drow the other day...
Sigh. I know. It's not the first time I've been robbed, I am only glad I didn't get hurt.
Hardly a soul on the Sword Coast has heard our kind's love chants. I've made a fair bit of coin performing them.
Our hearth is open, and there is safety beside it.
Will you sing a draconic song for me?
I don't think I've ever even been to our homeland... I know nothing of our clans.
Ah, you're a fearsome one! Fine by me, I'll get some shut-eye. Although I do sometimes whistle when I snore...
Oh, but she seems such a delight! Let her stay, at least for the night.
So you ran away from home?
Well, your life is poorer for it.
It's dangerous out there to be travelling on your own...
Thanks for the fire.
And have you said so? Do they know even one little bit of how you really feel?
Oh, there are sixty nine more verses, I'm only just beginning!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: As it ends, fade out to allow the player to escape

Text.Value: You wouldn't have half a bedroll for a lost minstrel, would you? I can pay for my board with music, if you care for it?
Who are you?
What's the worst that could happen?
Fine.
How do you write love songs, if you've never found love yourself?
Ah, the true language of love.
Wux-VOREL-EL-EL-EL-EL

EditorData.NodeContext: Like clawing nails down a chalkboard

Text.Value: Hark! Hark! A camp, and, Oghma-willing, some friendly faces.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player had their back to alfira, sitting at camp fire. At her voice the player stands up - turns to her in a combat ready stance.
EditorData.NodeContext: Has been wandering in the dark and FINALLY found the player's camp. Barges in and the player stands at her sudden arrival - combat ready. She's a little panicked and trying to calm the situation.

Text.Value: You can't stay - I have no time for weaklings.
I'll just stay one night, promise, then I'll be gone. I know I'm ice-blood, but I get cold so fast, I need to be by the fire.
Oh, let her stay. What's the worst that could happen?
Erm, on second thoughts, let's go to sleep.
Fine... if I must... but there's trouble out there, and I don't have so much as a butterknife on me.

EditorData.NodeContext: player has refused to let her stay - aboslutely gutted

Text.Value: She hardly seems a danger to us. Let the girl stay, if she's desperate enough to think our troupe good company.
My clan-name has been struck. I named myself anew after a long-dead poet.
Pfft. It's a miracle I'm still alive!
Quil Grootslang, soon to be published in the songbook Affairs in Ancient Abeir: Songs of Draconic Love. If I make it to Baldur's Gate with my manuscript, that is.
I'll never meet another like Lae'zel, that's for sure.
Ari-ARUX-UX-UX-UX-UX

EditorData.NodeContext: As dischordant and unpleasant to listen to as one can imagine

Text.Value: Run away.
Well, I'm sure it's of anthropological interest to someone.
Is there someone who you think you might love? Come on, I won't tell.
Then you are free...
My mind and loins are captive to thoughts of Halsin.
Gods, let her stay if she shuts the hells up.
Leave.
Astarion might be the most perfect being to ever walk the day.
You probably don't know, but the dragonborn clans arrange their children's marital unions. Love is considered irrelevant to egg-duty.

Synopsis:
In this scene, a dragonborn bard, Quil Grootslang arrives unannounced at the player's camp.
The player can tell them to leave or let them stay, but in either case in the next dialogue Quil will be dead.
